==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[dogge]], from {{OE.}} ''docga'' and Old English noun ''scit(t)e'', verb ''scitan'', from a Common Germanic ancestor.

===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): /dɒg/, /dQg/ /SIt/
*(''US''): /dɔːg/, /dO:g/ /SIt/

===Noun===
'''[[dog]] [[shit]]''' 

# {{vulgar}} [[fecal]] matter produced by a [[dog]]

